#
# valgrind suppressions for F-Stack unit tests (FU-S2-1).
#
# Stage-6 Phase-8 (FU-S2-2-CFG-UNLOAD) closed: lib/ff_config.c now exposes
# ff_unload_config() and registers it via atexit() at the end of the first
# ff_load_config(). Subsequent ff_load_config() calls also clear prior
# state. Repeated load/unload cycles in test harnesses no longer leak.
#
# As a result, this file currently holds NO entries: every leak detected by
# `make check` should be a real regression. If a future test legitimately
# needs to suppress a third-party (DPDK / cmocka / glibc) allocation, add
# a tightly-scoped block here with a justifying comment.
#
# Suppression syntax: see https://valgrind.org/docs/manual/manual-core.html#manual-core.suppress
#
